    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n(This is a repost of https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/3326.)\n\nI'd like neovim to automatically stop LSP clients when the filetype of a buffer changes to something no longer appropriate for that LSP.\n\nI found this Reddit thread sort of talking about this: https://www.reddit.com/r/neovim/comments/15h6f4o/lsp_is_started_even_though_i_change_the_filetype/, but I haven't been able to find any discussion over on neovim core.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen the filetype of a buffer changes, I expect now-irrelevant LSP clients to stop/detach from that buffer.",
